  "prompt": "What is it like to be an opera singer?",
  "response": "Being an opera singer can be a challenging and rewarding career. Here are some key aspects of the profession:\n\n1. Training\n- Extensive vocal training from a young age\n- Years of studying music theory, languages, and performance techniques\n- Formal education at conservatories or music schools\n\n2. Physical demands\n- Rigorous vocal exercises and practice\n- Maintaining vocal health\n- Strong breath control and physical stamina\n- Performing complex, lengthy roles\n\n3. Career challenges\n- Highly competitive field\n- Irregular income and employment\n- Frequent auditions\n- Often need to travel for performances\n- Limited number of professional opportunities\n\n4. Performance aspects\n- Performing in multiple languages\n- Acting while singing complex musical pieces\n- Wearing elaborate costumes\n- Memorizing lengthy scores\n- Performing in large venues with full orchestras\n\n5. Skills required\n- Exceptional musical talent\n- Strong stage presence\n- Emotional expressiveness\n- Discipline and dedication\n- Technical vocal skills\n- Physical and mental resilience\n\n6. Rewards\n- Performing beautiful, complex music\n- Artistic expression\n- Potential for international recognition\n- Connecting with audiences\n- Personal satisfaction of mastering a difficult art form\n\nThe life of an opera singer is demanding but can be deeply fulfilling for those passionate about the art form.",
